nodes.bodyText:
The search based approach is just using the element name to match the result, that is not accurate in some cases. Also it cannot find local variable.
For example, the sample code below is the decompiled source for Gson class, which contains two overload methods toGson. If i select the second method toGson and call findElementAtSelection, it will return me with the first toGson method, that's not accurate.
public final class Gson {
   ...
   public String toJson(Object src) {
      return src == null ? this.toJson((JsonElement)JsonNull.INSTANCE) : this.toJson((Object)src, (Type)src.getClass());
   }

   public String toJson(Object src, Type typeOfSrc) {
      StringWriter writer = new StringWriter();
      this.toJson(src, typeOfSrc, (Appendable)writer);
      return writer.toString();
   }
}

I'm thinking whether to have a better approach to resolve the selected element.

